    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-16T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-16T02:00:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/917: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-16T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 16, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>549. Reference my 527, April 11, 9 a.m. Ministry of Finance in a communication
                    signed by Dr. Kung has notified the Stabilization Board of the Ministry’s
                    proposal to grant a 50 cents on the dollar exchange allowance to foreign
                    diplomatic and consular establishments in China. The word “subsidy” is not
                    employed. The communication, somewhat lacking in precision with regard to
                    procedure and eventual accounting, requests the Board to give the matter its
                    attention.</p>
                <p>Adler,<note n="21" xml:id="d454fn21">Solomon Adler.</note> our member of the
                    Stabilization Board, will report fully after meeting of the Board for the
                    information of the Department and the Treasury.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vincent</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
